                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#32vb"/>                           
                           <desc type="Supplication">Supplication for the donor(s) and for the "people of
                              Ṗarāqliṭos". </desc>
                          <note> Zamikāʾel and his wife Fǝqǝrta Krǝstos (but cp.
                             Qǝddǝstä Krǝstos in the supplication formula on <locus target="#62ra">62ra</locus>) are mentioned. The note is written by the same hand as <ref type="hand" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESap008#a1">Additio 1
                              in AP-008</ref>. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#62rb"/>
                           <desc type="Excommunication">Excommunication against those who stole the book or erased
                              its text.</desc>

                           <note> Written by the same hand as Additio 1 (?). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>The title መ/. ግብረ ልኡካን "Maṣḥafa gǝbra lǝʾukan" is
                           written on the front board with yellow modern paint. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>Erasures:
                           e.g., <locus target="#14vb">14vb</locus>, 24vb, 44va, 48va, 55rb.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Corrections written interlineally: <locus target="#13ra">13ra</locus>,
                           32rb, 32vb, sometimes in the main, sometimes in a secondary hand.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc>Crude note: <locus target="#62rb">62rb</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"><desc>Crude doodles and
                           drawings in recent hands, in ink, pen and pencil: e.g., <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 2rv, 53v-57r, 59r, 129v, 130r.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e6"><desc>Shelfmark C3-IV-56  on <locus target="#63r">63r</locus></desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7"><desc>On some fols. the word qum or qʷǝm ("stop", "stand") is written in red by
                           a secondary hand (?) in the intercolumn or in the upper margin. In addition
                           a red curved line with one or two circle at each end is drawn occasionally
                           between two words of the main text (e.g., <locus target="#16r">16r</locus>,
                           17r, 94r, 101rb, 111ra). This term may indicate a particular passage of the
                           text or a certain section or may serve as a reminder for the reader to
                           command that the congregation "stands up" (cp. UhlPal 91).</desc></item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
